spirit:field.spirit:name: UE_STATUS
spirit:field.spirit:description: If ‘1’ an uncorrectable error has occurred. Cleared when ‘1’ is written to this bit position

spirit:field.spirit:name: CE_STATUS
spirit:field.spirit:description: If ‘1’ a correctable error has occurred. Cleared when ‘1’ is written to this bit position

spirit:field.spirit:name: UE_EN_IRQ
spirit:field.spirit:description: 1 - The value of the UE_STATUS bit of the ECC Status Register is propagated to the Interrupt signal. 0 - The value of the UE_STATUS bit of the ECC Status Register is not propagated to the Interrupt signal.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CE_EN_IRQ
spirit:field.spirit:description: 1 - The value of the CE_STATUS bit of the ECC Status Register is propagated to the Interrupt signal. 0 - The value of the CE_STATUS bit of the ECC Status Register is not propagated to the Interrupt signal.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ECC_ON_OFF
spirit:field.spirit:description: 0 - ECC checking is disabled on read operations. (ECC generation is enabled on write operations when C_ECC = 1). 1 - ECC checking is enabled on read operations. All correctable and uncorrectable error conditions are captured and status updated.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CE_CNT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Registers holds number of correctable errors encountered

spirit:register.spirit:name: CE_FFA0
spirit:register.spirit:displayName: Correctable Error First Failing Address Register 0
spirit:register.spirit:description: Correctable Error First Failing Address Register, bits [31:0]

spirit:field.spirit:name: CE_FFA0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Address (bits [31:0]) of the first occurrence of a correctable error

spirit:register.spirit:name: CE_FFA1
spirit:register.spirit:displayName: Correctable Error First Failing Address Register 1
spirit:register.spirit:description: Correctable Error First Failing Address Register, bits [63:32]

spirit:field.spirit:name: CE_FFA1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Address (bits [63:32]) of the first occurrence of a correctable error

spirit:register.spirit:name: UE_FFD1
spirit:register.spirit:displayName: Uncorrectable Error First Failing Data Register 1
spirit:register.spirit:description: Uncorrectable Error First Failing Data Register , bits [63:32]

spirit:field.spirit:name: UE_FFD
spirit:field.spirit:description: Data (bits [63:32) of the first occurrence of an uncorrectable error

spirit:register.spirit:name: UE_FFD2
spirit:register.spirit:displayName: Uncorrectable Error First Failing Data Register 2
spirit:register.spirit:description: Uncorrectable Error First Failing Data Register , bits [95:64]

spirit:field.spirit:name: UE_FFD
spirit:field.spirit:description: Data (bits [95:64]) of the first occurrence of an uncorrectable error

spirit:register.spirit:name: UE_FFD3
spirit:register.spirit:displayName: Uncorrectable Error First Failing Data Register 3
spirit:register.spirit:description: Uncorrectable Error First Failing Data Register , bits [127:96]

spirit:field.spirit:name: UE_FFD
spirit:field.spirit:description: Data (bits [127:96]) of the first occurrence of an uncorrectable error

spirit:field.spirit:name: FI_D0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit positions set to ‘1’ toggle the corresponding bits [31:0] of the next data word written to the block RAM. The register is automatically cleared after the fault has been injected.

spirit:field.spirit:name: FI_D1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit positions set to ‘1’ toggle the corresponding bits [63:32] of the next data word written to the block RAM. The register is automatically cleared after the fault has been injected.

spirit:field.spirit:name: FI_D2
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit positions set to ‘1’ toggle the corresponding bits [95:64] of the next data word written to the block RAM. The register is automatically cleared after the fault has been injected.

spirit:field.spirit:name: FI_D3
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit positions set to ‘1’ toggle the corresponding bits [127:96] of the next data word written to the block RAM. The register is automatically cleared after the fault has been injected.

spirit:field.spirit:name: FI_ECC
spirit:field.spirit:description: Bit positions set to ‘1’ toggle the corresponding bit of the next ECC written to the block RAM. The register is automatically cleared after the fault has been injected.
